1
00:00:02,296 --> 00:00:05,917
I was on a train once,
in India.

2
00:00:05,917 --> 00:00:09,174
There was a wife, her husband,
and their child.

3
00:00:09,384 --> 00:00:12,021
[A Loving Eye Conceals Defects]

4
00:00:12,921 --> 00:00:16,301
The wife looks like
a Bollywood actress,

5
00:00:16,301 --> 00:00:19,203
she’s like world-class beauty.

6
00:00:19,203 --> 00:00:22,107
But this is India, 
the land of arranged marriages;

7
00:00:22,107 --> 00:00:24,959
her husband, 
and I’m not saying this as a criticism,

8
00:00:24,959 --> 00:00:30,744
but just as a statement and
as a fact, was hideously ugly—

9
00:00:30,747 --> 00:00:33,039
not just unattractive.

10
00:00:33,039 --> 00:00:35,929
Like acid had been thrown
all over his face.

11
00:00:35,929 --> 00:00:38,697
Worse than the phantom of the opera. 
Hideous, like

12
00:00:38,697 --> 00:00:43,369
if you accidentally saw his face,
you’d go, “Oh, God.”

13
00:00:43,369 --> 00:00:45,611
That type of … 
I’m not talking about someone

14
00:00:45,611 --> 00:00:47,444
who’s just not attractive,
not like that; 
 

15
00:00:47,444 --> 00:00:52,143
something had obviously happened,
some kind of a chemical accident.

16
00:00:52,143 --> 00:00:58,351
So his face was melted,
ugly … hideous.

17
00:00:58,351 --> 00:01:02,076
His wife looks like 
a Bollywood actress.

18
00:01:02,076 --> 00:01:09,230
And I saw, I was stunned,
because the little child

19
00:01:09,245 --> 00:01:14,355
was looking with this love 
and affection at her father,

20
00:01:14,355 --> 00:01:18,423
and the father’s beaming love
and affection towards the child,

21
00:01:18,423 --> 00:01:21,353
and the wife 
is beaming love and affection
 

22
00:01:21,353 --> 00:01:23,723
towards her husband 
and her child,

23
00:01:23,723 --> 00:01:25,843
as if to say—
they’re saying like,

24
00:01:25,843 --> 00:01:30,789
“We are so fortunate, 
we have this loving family situation.

25
00:01:30,789 --> 00:01:32,773
Aren’t we fortunate people?

26
00:01:32,773 --> 00:01:37,492
Are there more fortunate people 
than us in the world?”

27
00:01:37,492 --> 00:01:39,964
That was their mood.

28
00:01:39,964 --> 00:01:42,624
And I remind you
Guru Mahārāj’s saying,

29
00:01:42,624 --> 00:01:46,038
“Love can accommodate everything,

30
00:01:46,038 --> 00:01:50,200
it conceals whatever looks unsightly,

31
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:52,484
what has a flaw, 
what’s ugly …”

32
00:01:52,484 --> 00:01:59,364
what’s … 
how do you say,

33
00:01:59,364 --> 00:02:02,115
what’s the word 
for a bad behavioral trait?

34
00:02:02,115 --> 00:02:06,134
Anyway I can’t speak properly 
right now—

35
00:02:06,134 --> 00:02:10,087
a character flaw, whatever.
So he’s saying,

36
00:02:10,087 --> 00:02:12,650
“When the finite is trying 
to approach the Infinite, 
 

37
00:02:12,650 --> 00:02:18,550
how is that going to work?
How is that even possible?”

38
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:21,197
He’s saying,
“Through love and affection.”

39
00:02:21,197 --> 00:02:24,595
That’s how the smallest 
can connect to the Greatest.

40
00:02:24,595 --> 00:02:28,049
This is why he says, 
“Love, beauty over power.”

41
00:02:28,049 --> 00:02:32,122
The greatest power
in the world,

42
00:02:32,122 --> 00:02:35,204
the greatest force in the world
is not power,

43
00:02:35,204 --> 00:02:38,678
but beauty, love, 
charm, and sweetness,

44
00:02:38,678 --> 00:02:42,888
which is personified
in Kṛṣṇa conception.

45
00:02:42,888 --> 00:02:45,091
That’s beauty, love.
We just spoke something

46
00:02:45,091 --> 00:02:48,269
of the beauty, love, 
and charm of Rāmachandra,

47
00:02:48,269 --> 00:02:55,917
but somewhat constricted 
by the position of being a king

48
00:02:55,917 --> 00:02:57,785
and governing and all that.

49
00:02:57,785 --> 00:03:03,148
Whereas in Kṛṣṇa conception
the full expression

50
00:03:03,148 --> 00:03:08,080
of love and sweetness
is unleashed and

51
00:03:10,827 --> 00:03:14,106
expressed to the extreme.

52
00:03:14,688 --> 00:03:23,819
So that’s why
we’re approaching Kṛṣṇa.

